## ğŸ’¬ Step 2 â€” Create and Configure Your Telegram Bot

Youâ€™ll need a Telegram bot that can talk to your Gswarm instance.  
This only takes a couple of minutes.

### ğŸª„ 1. Create a New Bot
1. Open Telegram and start a chat with **[@BotFather](https://t.me/BotFather)**  
2. Type `/newbot`  
3. Follow the prompts to name your bot and choose a username  
4. When itâ€™s done, copy the **bot token** that BotFather gives you â€” youâ€™ll need it later

### ğŸ†” 2. Find Your Chat ID
1. Open Telegram and send a message to your new bot (like â€œhelloâ€)  
2. In your browser, go to this link â€” replacing `<YOUR_BOT_TOKEN>` with the token from BotFather:
   ```
   https://api.telegram.org/bot<YOUR_BOT_TOKEN>/getUpdates
   ```
3. Youâ€™ll see a JSON response. Look for a section that says:
   ```json
   "chat": { "id": 123456789 }
   ```
   That number is your **chat ID** â€” keep it safe.

ğŸ’¡ *If you see no results (`"result":[]`), send another message to your bot and refresh the page.*

